findAll

Iterable<DataType> findAll()
Shortcut method allowing to return all instances of DataType. Implementors are left free to implement or not this method. But, were it not to be implemented, I (riduidel) suggest one throws an UnsupportedOperationException

Returns:
an iterable allowing one to brows the whole stored objects. This Iterable is NOT meant to be modifiable. As a consequence, Iterator generated by this Iterable is left free to not support the remove operation.
